  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Once you have <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933344786/Creating+a+Customer+Profile\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933344786\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">added a customer to RepairQ</a>, you may need to make changes to their contact and marketing information, credit balances, etc.</p><p>If you need assistance with other customer management features, check out these articles:</p><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931116664/Customer+Ticket+and+Device+History\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931116664\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Customer Ticket and Device History</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933541687/Adding+and+Applying+Credit+Balances+for+Customers\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933541687\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Adjusting Credit Balances</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934491696/Appointments\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934491696\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointments Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803749/Customer+Communication+Preferences+and+Marketing+List\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803749\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Marketing List</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933869089/Required+Fields+for+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933869089\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Validation Rules for Customers</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2036891839/Zip+Code+Validation+for+Customers\" data-linked-resource-id=\"2036891839\" data-linked-resource-version=\"2\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Zip Code Validation for Customers</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"ManagingCustomerProfiles-EditingCustomersinRepairQ\">Editing Customers in RepairQ</h2><p /><p>1. Users can <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933377743/Customer+Search\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933377743\" data-linked-resource-version=\"14\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">quick-search for a customer</a> or use the Navigation Bar to go to <strong>Customers</strong> \u2192 <strong>View Customers</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"442\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Edit%20Customer%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Customer Overview page, you can search for customers by keyword or filter by category. If your search yields a single match, you will be taken to their profile page. On the Customer Summary, you can click Edit on the right side to make changes.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Edit%20Customer%202.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Edit%20Customer%202.5.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>You can also edit directly from the Customer List. Locate the customer and click on the <strong>Options</strong> button under Actions, and click <strong>Edit</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Edit%20Customer%203.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"102\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Edit%20Customer%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. An Edit Customer pop-up will appear. There are additional categories on the left side of the window to guide you through the data fields. Add information at your discretion. Once you are satisfied with your changes, click <strong>Save</strong> at the bottom of the window.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933312070/Edit%20Customer%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note:</strong> There may be additional required fields when updating a customer if there have been changes to <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933869089/Required+Fields+for+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933869089\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Customer Validation</a> settings. If <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2036891839/Zip+Code+Validation+for+Customers\" data-linked-resource-id=\"2036891839\" data-linked-resource-version=\"2\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Zip Code validation</a> is active, the user will be required to enter a valid zip code for every customer.</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
